&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gateshead Health NHS Foundation Trust &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Older Persons Community Mental Health Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gateshead Specialist Memory Hub&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff Nurse RMN - Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a high performing Trust with opportunities for nurses who are motivated and passionate about delivering high standards of patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Gateshead Specialist Memory Hub is a resource based at Bensham Hospital. We provide treatment, post diagnostic support and education for patients with dementia aswell as carer support both within the Hub and in collaboration with external agencies. We also refer and signpost to other services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer programmes of Cognitive Stimulation Therapy within the Hub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated individual to join an innovative team of nurses. We are looking for a Band 5 Staff Nurse RMN (15 hours per week) with drive to champion the 6 C’s in nursing. You should be able to demonstrate excellent leadership, communication and organisational skills. You should have experience in working with older persons within mental health services and have sound clinical knowledge. Applications are welcomed from newly qualified nurses as training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be expected to work flexibly in order to meet the needs of patients/carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries are welcomed by Susan Dodds, Memory Hub Manager on 0191 4456660.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to DBS (Police Bureau) – ENHANCED Disclosure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
